  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "7:14-24 Every faithful minister may humbly adopt Christ's words. His doctrine is not his own finding out, but is from God's word, through the teaching of his Spirit. And amidst the disputes which disturb the world, if any man, of any nation, seeks to do the will of God, he shall know whether the doctrine is of God, or whether men speak of themselves. Only those who hate the truth shall be given up to errors which will be fatal. Surely it was as agreeable to the design of the sabbath to restore health to the afflicted, as to administer an outward rite. Jesus told them to decide on his conduct according to the spiritual import of the Divine law. We must not judge concerning any by their outward appearance, but by their worth, and by the gifts and graces of God's Spirit in them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That speaketh of himself - This does not mean about or concerning himself, but he that speaks by his own authority, without being sent by God, as mere human teachers do.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Seeketh his own glory - His own praise, or seeks for reputation and applause. This is the case with mere human teachers, and as Jesus in his discourses manifestly sought to honor God, they ought to have supposed that he was sent by him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "No unrighteousness - This word here means, evidently, there is no falsehood, no deception in him. He is not an impostor. It is used in the same sense in 2 Thessalonians 2:10-12. It is true that there was no unrighteousness, no sin in Jesus Christ, but that is not the truth taught here. It is that he was not an impostor, and the evidence of this was that he sought not his own glory, but the honor of God. This evidence was furnished:",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "No unrighteousness - This word here means, evidently, there is no falsehood, no deception in him. He is not an impostor. It is used in the same sense in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Thessalonians 2:10-12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". It is true that there was no unrighteousness, no sin in Jesus Christ, but that is not the truth taught here. It is that he was not an impostor, and the evidence of this was that he sought not his own glory, but the honor of God. This evidence was furnished:",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1. in his retiring, unobtrusive disposition; in his not seeking the applause of people;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. in his teaching such doctrines as tended to exalt God and humble man;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3. in his ascribing all glory and praise to God; ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "3. in his ascribing all glory and praise to God; ",
            "children": []
